rComments: I really enjoyed Prof. Marier's class this semester! He clearly cares a lot about helping students succeed. There was no textbook, but lot's of online readings. He gave some great insight on what working in journalism is like, and provided feedback with that in mind. I would absolutely recommend his class, especially if you're in fourth year.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Prof Marier is a great prof, you can tell he really cares about his students and their success. He is very fair and wants to make sure you're learning instead of just memorizing content to regurgitate it.

He is very organized. He is also very flexible in his schedule. Great teacher and grader. Is JOU classes are very hands-on which is a fun change. I would absolutely recommend him to anyone. He is also perfectly bilingual, so taking him in English or french classes make no difference.

He gives SO many assignments but at least there isn't a midterm or final. His expectations for the assignments are clear. His classes are dry and boring though. What's good is that he always talks about working as a journalist which really gives you an insight in the career.
His syllabus is the most detailed thing ever! You know exactly what you're supposed to do!

Knows his stuff about journalism! Shared lots of important industry techniques. Big final digital article assignment at the end, hard to balance with exams so start early! Lots of mini projects that are quite a bit of work worth barely any marks, sometimes they were a little annoying to complete.  Interesting content being applied.  Great guy

Il est un excellent professeur. Même s'il travail beaucoup avec son emploi à Radio-Canada, il est toujours présent pour ses élèves et il est toujours prêt à aider. Il n'est pas le simple professeur à venir a l'école que pour enseigner. Il vient car il aime le domaine qu'il enseigne, le journalisme, et il prend soin des élèves. Excellent professeur!
